<paragraph id="8BB4368CFFE0FFA551E9DD89FCB03826" blockId="16.[189,1399,408,582]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Hypopygium longer than wide; anterior stalk slender and long; posterior margin with branches short and wide. Genitalia with paramere apex sparsely hairy; ventral arm of paramere sinuous and slender; aedeagus slender, with apex aligned with paramere apex, apical margin rounded, and with short outer projection, lateral margin of basal portion slightly convex.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3116507FFE0FFA551E9DE5BFCB23E44" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB4368CFFE0FFA551E9DE5BFEF738E9" blockId="16.[189,303,623,649]" box="[189,303,623,649]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading id="D0FC81E0FFE0FFA551E9DE5BFEF738E9" bold="true" box="[189,303,623,649]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B97FEA9EFFE0FFA551E9DE5BFEF738E9" bold="true" box="[189,303,623,649]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4368CFFE0FFA551E9DEABFB4E392D" blockId="16.[189,1399,671,845]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
This species was originally described in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D0FFFE0FFA553DDDEABFC1B38DA" authority="(Costa 1864)" baseAuthorityName="Costa" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[649,963,671,698]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Sclerodermus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FEA9EFFE0FFA553DDDEABFCF138D9" box="[649,809,671,697]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Sclerodermus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B7DFFE0FFA55261DEABFC6338DA" author="Costa A. C. H." box="[821,955,671,698]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 176" refId="ref7289" refString="Costa A. C. H. 1864. Anno II - 1862 con quattro tavole. Parte prima et seconda. Annuario del Museo Zoologico della R. Universita di Napoli 2: 1 - 176." type="journal article" year="1864">Costa 1864</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
based on one female from 
<collectingCountry id="F31C761CFFE0FFA555A6DEABFAF238D9" box="[1266,1322,671,697]" name="Italy" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Italy</collectingCountry>
. It was transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D0FFFE0FFA55031DEF1FE1038BE" box="[357,456,709,734]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Mesitius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FEA9EFFE0FFA55031DEF1FE1038BE" box="[357,456,709,734]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Mesitius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B7DFFE0FFA550ACDEF0FD7E38BE" author="Kieffer J. - J." box="[504,678,708,734]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="228 - 595" refId="ref7541" refString="Kieffer J. - J. 1914. Bethylidae. Das Tierreich 41: 228 - 595." type="journal article" year="1914">Kieffer (1914)</bibRefCitation>
, who synonymised 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D0FFFE0FFA552C7DEF0FB6638BE" box="[915,1214,708,734]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Sclerodermus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mutilloides">
<emphasis id="B97FEA9EFFE0FFA552C7DEF0FB6638BE" box="[915,1214,708,734]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Sclerodermus mutilloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D0FFFE0FFA55447DEF1FE0B3964" authority="Spinola, 1851" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1851" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Mesitius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ghilianii">
<emphasis id="B97FEA9EFFE0FFA55447DEF1FEF83963" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Mesitius ghilianii</emphasis>
Spinola, 1851
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B7DFFE0FFA5508BDEDDFD7B3963" author="Argaman Q." box="[479,675,745,771]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="61 - 96" refId="ref7029" refString="Argaman Q. 2003. Generic synopsis of Mesitinae Kieffer, 1914 (Hymenoptera: Bethylidae). Entomofauna 24: 61 - 96." type="journal article" year="2003">Argaman (2003)</bibRefCitation>
revalidated the status as a valid species and transferred this species from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D0FFFE0FFA55008DF3BFE673948" box="[348,447,783,808]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Mesitius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FEA9EFFE0FFA55008DF3BFE673948" box="[348,447,783,808]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Mesitius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D0FFFE0FFA550BCDF3AFDAB3948" authorityName="Nagy" authorityYear="1972" box="[488,627,782,808]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Clytrovorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FEA9EFFE0FFA550BCDF3AFDAB3948" box="[488,627,782,808]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Clytrovorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Argaman also established the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D0FFFE0FFA555DEDF3BFE8D392D" authority="Kieffer, 1906" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Mesitius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscicornis">
<emphasis id="B97FEA9EFFE0FFA555DEDF3BFAAF3948" box="[1162,1399,782,808]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Mesitius fuscicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B7DFFE0FFA551E9DF07FE8D392D" author="Kieffer J. - J." box="[189,341,819,845]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="289 - 551" refId="ref7501" refString="Kieffer J. - J. 1906. Proctotrypides. In: Andre E. (ed.) Species des hymenopteres d'Europe &amp; d'Algerie. Vol. 9: 289 - 551. A. Hermann, Paris." type="journal article" year="1906">Kieffer,1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D0FFFE0FFA55035DF00FD5A392D" authority="Hoffer, 1936" authorityName="Hoffer" authorityYear="1936" box="[353,642,819,845]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Mesitius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zavadili">
<emphasis id="B97FEA9EFFE0FFA55035DF00FE3D392D" box="[353,485,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">M. zavadili</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B7DFFE0FFA550B8DF07FD5A392D" author="Hoffer A." box="[492,642,819,845]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="119 - 124" refId="ref7411" refString="Hoffer A. 1936. Rod Mesitius Thoms. v Ceskoslovenske republice. Genus Mesitius Thoms. in der Cechoslovakei. (Bethylidae, Hym. - Vespoid.). Acta Societatis entomologicae cechosloveniae 33: 119 - 124." type="journal article" year="1936">Hoffer, 1936</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D0FFFE0FFA553EFDF00FC6F392D" authority="Nagy, 1968" authorityName="Nagy" authorityYear="1968" box="[699,951,819,845]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Mesitius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viator">
<emphasis id="B97FEA9EFFE0FFA553EFDF00FCF0392D" box="[699,808,820,845]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">M. viator</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B7DFFE0FFA5527BDF07FC6F392D" author="Nagy C. G." box="[815,951,819,845]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="168 - 176" refId="ref7737" refString="Nagy C. G. 1968. A new record of Mesitinae (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae). Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 47: 168 - 176." type="journal article" year="1968">Nagy, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
under this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4368CFFE0FFA551E9DF43FCB23E44" blockId="16.[189,1399,886,1060]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
We did not have access either to the 
<typeStatus id="54B0882EFFE0FFA55309DF43FD4A39F1" box="[605,658,887,913]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
, which is lost, or to any other voucher specimens of this species, and the original descriptions are not sufficiently detailed to compare with the diagnostic characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D0FFFE0FFA55188DFF4FEA339BA" authority="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo, 2019" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2019" box="[220,379,960,986]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Astromesitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97FEA9EFFE0FFA55188DFF4FEA339BA" box="[220,379,960,986]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Astromesitius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C57E5FFE0FFA550D5DFF4FE3339BA" box="[385,491,960,986]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
However, the illustration by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B7DFFE0FFA5526FDFF4FC2339BA" author="Argaman Q." box="[827,1019,960,986]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="61 - 96" refId="ref7029" refString="Argaman Q. 2003. Generic synopsis of Mesitinae Kieffer, 1914 (Hymenoptera: Bethylidae). Entomofauna 24: 61 - 96." type="journal article" year="2003">Argaman (2003)</bibRefCitation>
is clear and sufficient to analyze and reallocate this species from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D0FFFE0FFA5536FDFD1FD1E399F" authorityName="Nagy" authorityYear="1972" box="[571,710,997,1023]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Clytrovorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FEA9EFFE0FFA5536FDFD1FD1E399F" box="[571,710,997,1023]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Clytrovorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D0FFFE0FFA553BADFD1FC55399F" authority="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo, 2019" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2019" box="[750,909,997,1023]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Astromesitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97FEA9EFFE0FFA553BADFD1FC55399F" box="[750,909,997,1023]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Astromesitius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C57E5FFE0FFA552C1DFD1FBDC399F" box="[917,1028,997,1023]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, because it has long and sparse antennal pubescence and the hypopygium is ‘star-shaped’.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
